properties.Title: Update: High Water Advisory Alert For Portions Of The Red River
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for the Red River at Ste. Agathe, the Red River Floodway Inlet Control Structure, and within the City of Winnipeg due to expected high flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by the local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.

properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Poor visibility in snow and blowing snow is expected or occurring in some locations. A frontal system will move across the northern Yukon tonight. Snow has begun over southern sections of Dempster region this afternoon and will spread to the north this evening. Strong easterly winds will develop early this evening near the Richardson Mountains. Strong winds combined with snow will generate blowing snow and lower the visibility to 800 metres or less tonight near the Richardson Mountains. Conditions will improve overnight as the wind weakens. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility in some locations. Visibility may be significantly and suddenly reduced to near zero. Blowing snow advisories are issued when winds are expected to create blowing snow giving poor visibility to 800 metres or less for at least 3 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather in British Columbia or Yukon, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm or #YTStorm.
Expires: 2019-10-24T13:59:06-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2019-10-23T23:02:06-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.2419837927.2019
Area: Dempster
properties.Author: Environment Canada

properties.Title: Wreckhouse Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong winds are expected or occurring. Maximum wind gusts: locally gusts up to 110 km/h in the Wreckhouse area. Timespan: ending this morning. Remarks: Southeasterly winds will ease upon shifting to westerly early this morning. ### Very strong winds may push your vehicle around especially on roads through mountain passes and along deep valleys. Wreckhouse wind warnings are issued when there is a significant risk of damaging winds. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.
Expires: 2019-10-24T13:59:24-00:00

Area: Channel-Port aux Basques and vicinity
